---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Collapsible from '../components/Collapsible.astro';
import Sidenote from '../components/Sidenote.astro';
import HoverCard from '../components/HoverCard.astro';
import Window from '../components/Window.astro';
import WindowManager from '../components/WindowManager.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
	title="Paul Diaz Ashot"
	description="Founder-operator. Founding team at GMX. Active Claude developer. London, Barcelona, New York."
>
	<main class="cv">
		<header class="cv-header">
			<h1>Paul Diaz Ashot</h1>
			<div class="locations">London, Barcelona, New York</div>
			<div class="contact">
				<a href="mailto:paul.ashot@icloud.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">paul.ashot@icloud.com</a> ·
				(646) 996 5037 ·
				<a href="https://pauldiazashot.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">pauldiazashot.com</a> ·
				@supersonicsines
			</div>
		</header>

		<div class="cv-body">
			<Collapsible title="Introduction">
				<p>
					I am a founder-operator. I have been selling since I was 12. First it was paintings, now it's ideas. I spent four years on the founding team of <button type="button" class="inline-preview-trigger" data-window-trigger="preview-gmx" aria-haspopup="dialog"><b>GMX</b></button>, where I handled go-to-market and onboarded major partners. I spent four years running a venture consultancy practice alongside and after it, where I helped portfolio companies raise funding and pivot strategies to become profitable. My current obsession is deploying AI agents to automate and scale real businesses. Native English, fluent Russian, fluent Spanish; <Sidenote id="right-to-work" term="right to work in the UK, US, and EU">UK indefinite leave to remain status holder + US/EU dual national.</Sidenote>.
				</p>
				<p>
					Each role below opens as a window — click to read more. The PDF version is
					<a href="/Paul_Diaz_Ashot_CV.pdf" download target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>.
				</p>
			</Collapsible>

			<Collapsible title="Experience">
				<div class="role">
					<button class="role-trigger" data-window-trigger="portico" aria-haspopup="dialog">
						<b>Portico Ventures</b> — <em>Managing Partner</em>
					</button>
					<div class="dates">2021 – 2026</div>
				</div>
				<ul>
					<li>
						Venture consultancy advising early-stage DeFi and fintech founders.
						Three portfolio companies including <button type="button" class="inline-preview-trigger" data-window-trigger="preview-gammaswap" aria-haspopup="dialog"><b>Gammaswap</b></button>
						and <button type="button" class="inline-preview-trigger" data-window-trigger="preview-codex" aria-haspopup="dialog"><b>Codex</b></button>.
						Influenced <b>$4M+ in aggregate fundraising</b> through advisory work and warm introductions.
					</li>
				</ul>

				<div class="role">
					<button class="role-trigger" data-window-trigger="gmx" aria-haspopup="dialog">
						<b>GMX</b> — <em>Founding Team · Growth &amp; Partnerships</em>
					</button>
					<div class="dates">2020 – 2023</div>
				</div>
				<ul>
					<li>
						Three-person founding team. Top DeFi revenue generator during my tenure.
						Co-led institutional partnerships and capital formation; personally sourced
						<b>$20M+ in cumulative capital deployments</b>.
					</li>
					<li>
						Closed and co-closed strategic partnerships with <Sidenote id="arbitrum" term="Arbitrum">Arbitrum is an L2 for Ethereum that GMX utilised for lower transaction costs. Part of being an early adopter was negotiating for grants and trader rebates worth $10M+. <a href="https://gmxio.substack.com/p/how-gmx-will-utilise-the-12-million" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Read the GMX Arbitrum incentive post</a>.</Sidenote>, <Sidenote id="avalanche" term="Avalanche">The Avalanche Rush deployment incentive was one of the biggest incentive packages secured in DeFi at the time. The $4M in trading rewards led to eight-figure increases in TVL within a few months. <a href="https://medium.com/avalancheavax/gmx-joins-avalanche-rush-with-4m-in-trading-rewards-ce5c66f0e3b3" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Read the Avalanche Rush announcement</a>.</Sidenote>, <b>Chainlink</b>, and <b>Frax</b>, plus two other protocol integrations. Coordinated the <HoverCard term="Gambit → GMX rebrand">
							<span class="hc-p">The rebrand wasn't a marketing exercise; it was a chain migration from BSC (Gambit) to Arbitrum and Avalanche (GMX), with the partner network lined up to launch alongside.</span>
							<span class="hc-p"><em>[PLACEHOLDER — replace with 150–200 word account: why the rebrand was technically necessary, your specific role, timeline coordination across partners.]</em></span>
						</HoverCard> and organised outreach to future partners.
					</li>
					<li>
						Built and led the institutional and community channels: <b>5,000+ Telegram members</b> and direct relationships with eight-figure liquidity providers.
					</li>
				</ul>

				<div class="role">
					<button class="role-trigger" data-window-trigger="effie" aria-haspopup="dialog">
						<b>Effie Perine LTD.</b> — <em>Operations &amp; Client Relations</em>
					</button>
					<div class="dates">2019 – 2020</div>
				</div>
				<ul>
					<li>
						Managed financial accounts and operational administration for a private art dealership specialising in Old Master Pictures; annual transaction volumes in the £500K–£2.5M+ range.
					</li>
				</ul>
			</Collapsible>

			<Collapsible title="Current AI Deployments">
				<ul>
					<li>
						<HoverCard term="Pawlymarket">
							<span class="hc-p">Live scraper and statistical-arbitrage layer over prediction markets. Reads order books across Kalshi, Polymarket, and smaller venues; identifies systematic mispricings; surfaces them as actionable calls.</span>
							<span class="hc-p"><em>[PLACEHOLDER — replace with 150 words on engineering architecture (scrape-aggregator, statistical model layer, P&amp;L attribution), revenue trajectory, lessons learned. Embed dashboard screenshot.]</em></span>
							<span class="hc-p further-reading">→ <a href="https://pawlymarket.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">pawlymarket.com</a></span>
						</HoverCard> — live scraper and data aggregator using statistical models to identify market inefficiencies. <b>$50K ARR</b> within two months of launch. <a href="https://pawlymarket.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">pawlymarket.com</a>.
					</li>
					<li>
						<Sidenote id="vinted" term="Vinted-to-Depop reselling agent"><em>[PLACEHOLDER — 75 words]</em> An end-to-end autonomous fashion-arbitrage agent operating across Vinted and Depop. Driven by Claude through a Telegram interface; sources items, calculates margins, lists, fulfills.</Sidenote> — end-to-end autonomous fashion-arbitrage agent operated via Telegram.
					</li>
					<li>
						<Sidenote id="booking" term="Intelligent booking system"><em>[PLACEHOLDER — 50 words]</em> Claude-powered scheduler for a small local business. Takes class bookings, reschedules around capacity constraints, and organises future classes from predicted demand.</Sidenote> — Claude-powered agentic scheduler for a small local business; takes class bookings and organises future classes based on predicted demand.
					</li>
				</ul>
			</Collapsible>

			<Collapsible title="Education" open={false}>
				<p>
					<b>BSc Chemistry</b>, <em>University of Manchester</em>, 2018.
				</p>
			</Collapsible>

			<Collapsible title="Skills" open={false}>
				<p class="skills">
					Consultative selling to technical buyers · enterprise negotiation · founder-network leverage · community-led growth · technical product evangelism · venture capital · startup operations · risk management · marketing outreach · financial modelling · Claude API · Claude Code · prompt engineering · agentic workflows · MCP · Python · JavaScript
				</p>
			</Collapsible>
		</div>

		<footer class="cv-footer">
			<a href="mailto:paul.ashot@icloud.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">paul.ashot@icloud.com</a> ·
			@supersonicsines ·
			<a href="/Paul_Diaz_Ashot_CV.pdf" download target="_blank" rel="noopener">Download CV (PDF)</a>
		</footer>
	</main>

	<!-- External preview windows -->
	<Window
		id="preview-gmx"
		title="https://gmx.io"
		initialX={154}
		initialY={96}
		initialWidth={640}
		initialHeight={388}
		resizable={false}
		variant="preview"
	>
		<div class="external-preview">
			<img src="/previews/gmx.png" alt="Preview of https://gmx.io" loading="lazy" />
			<a class="external-preview-arrow" href="https://gmx.io" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" aria-label="Open https://gmx.io">→</a>
		</div>
	</Window>

	<Window
		id="preview-gammaswap"
		title="https://gammaswap.com"
		initialX={176}
		initialY={112}
		initialWidth={640}
		initialHeight={388}
		resizable={false}
		variant="preview"
	>
		<div class="external-preview">
			<img src="/previews/gammaswap.png" alt="Preview of https://gammaswap.com" loading="lazy" />
			<a class="external-preview-arrow" href="https://gammaswap.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" aria-label="Open https://gammaswap.com">→</a>
		</div>
	</Window>

	<Window
		id="preview-codex"
		title="https://www.codex.io"
		initialX={220}
		initialY={144}
		initialWidth={640}
		initialHeight={388}
		resizable={false}
		variant="preview"
	>
		<div class="external-preview">
			<img src="/previews/codex.png" alt="Preview of https://www.codex.io" loading="lazy" />
			<a class="external-preview-arrow" href="https://www.codex.io" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" aria-label="Open https://www.codex.io">→</a>
		</div>
	</Window>

	<!-- Role windows -->
	<Window id="portico" title="Portico Ventures · Managing Partner" initialX={140} initialY={100}>
		<p><b>Portico Ventures</b> — <em>Managing Partner, 2021 – 2026</em></p>
		<p>
			Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Sed do eiusmod
			tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim
			veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex
			ea commodo consequat.
